getPlayerName

public String getPlayerName(String name)
Attempts to resolve the full Player-Name by a portion of it. Note: Uses getOfflinePlayer(java.lang.String) to obtain the player-name.

Parameters:
name - The partial name to search.
Returns:
The player name, if the player could not be found, null.
See Also:
getOfflinePlayer(String)

getPlayer

public static org.bukkit.entity.Player getPlayer(String name)
Attempts to resolve a player by a partial name.

The following order is used to match player names:

  • The exact player name, case insensitive.
  • The start of the player name, case insensitive.
  • The contents of the player name, case insensitive.
  • The start of the player's custom name, case insensitive.
  • The contents of the player's custom name, case insensitive.

Parameters:
name - The partial name to match.
Returns:
The player. If the player could not be found, null.

getOfflinePlayer

public static org.bukkit.OfflinePlayer getOfflinePlayer(String name)
Attempts to resolve a player (online or offline) by a partial name.

Uses getOfflinePlayer(String, boolean) with the second parameter as true.

See Also:
getOfflinePlayer(String)

getOfflinePlayer

public static org.bukkit.OfflinePlayer getOfflinePlayer(String name,
                                                        boolean onlineCheck)
Attempts to resolve an (Offline) player by a partial name.

The following order is used to match player names:

  • The exact player name, case insensitive.

    • Parameters:
    name - The partial name to match.
    onlineCheck - If true, the online players will be matched first.
    Returns:
    The player. If the player could not be found, null.

concatPlayerNames

public static String concatPlayerNames(Collection<org.bukkit.OfflinePlayer> players)
Returns a String of concatenated player names.

Example: 

 concatPlayerNames(Arrays.asString(new String[]{"Notch", "DarthSalamon", "EvilPerson"}); // Notch, DarthSalamon, EvilPerson

Parameters:
players - The players to concatenate.
Returns:
The resulting String.
